{%- comment -%}
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BREADCRUMB
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Custom addition to the Impact theme, not part of Maestrooo's base code. Rendered once from layout/theme.liquid so every
page gets the same trail, instead of editing each main-* section and fighting them on the next theme update.

********************************************
Where the hierarchy comes from
********************************************

Shopify collections are a flat list, there is no parent/child relation to read. The only place the catalogue is
organised in levels is the navigation menu, so the parent level is looked up in the main menu: a collection that appears
as a sub-item of "Boosters et packs" gets that entry inserted before it.

Consequence to keep in mind: re-organising the main menu re-organises the breadcrumb. That is intended, it keeps a
single place to maintain. A collection absent from the menu simply has no parent level, which is the previous behaviour.

The menu handle is hardcoded to 'main-menu' because the header reads its menu from a section setting, which a layout
snippet cannot access. Verified in sections/header-group.json: the header is set to "main-menu".

********************************************
Structured data
********************************************

This snippet emits the BreadcrumbList JSON-LD itself, from the exact same variables it renders, so what a shopper reads
and what Google indexes can never drift. The BreadcrumbList that Impact used to emit in snippets/microdata-schema.liquid
was removed for that reason: two BreadcrumbList on one page compete, and that one ignored the parent level.

********************************************
Placement note
********************************************

This renders before the first section inside <main>, so `[role="main"] .shopify-section:first-child` no longer matches
and `--section-is-first` stays 0. That variable is read only by the transparent-header rules (theme.css line 842 and the
`allow_transparent_header` blocks in collection-banner, image-with-text-overlay, main-article, main-blog, slideshow and
video). `allow_transparent_header` is false on every template of this store, verified on 21/07/2026, so nothing changes
today. If a first section is ever switched to a transparent header, hide the breadcrumb on that page, otherwise the
section is pulled up by the header height and covers it.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign show_breadcrumb = true

  case request.page_type
    when 'index', 'password', 'captcha', 'gift_card'
      assign show_breadcrumb = false
  endcase

  case request.page_type
    when 'product'
      assign current_title = product.title
    when 'collection'
      assign current_title = collection.title
    when 'blog'
      assign current_title = blog.title
    when 'article'
      assign current_title = article.title
    when 'page'
      assign current_title = page.title
    when 'cart'
      assign current_title = 'cart.general.title' | t
    when 'search'
      assign current_title = 'search.general.title' | t
    when '404'
      assign current_title = '404.general.title' | t
    else
      assign current_title = page_title
  endcase

  comment
    The collection that leads to the current page: itself on a collection page, the one the shopper came from on a
    product page. On a product reached from a search or a direct link it stays empty, and the trail is Home > product.
  endcomment

  assign trail_collection = null

  if request.page_type == 'collection' or request.page_type == 'product'
    if collection.url != blank and collection.handle != 'all'
      assign trail_collection = collection
    endif
  endif

  assign parent_title = ''
  assign parent_url = ''

  if trail_collection != null
    for top_link in linklists['main-menu'].links
      if top_link.url == trail_collection.url
        break
      endif

      for child_link in top_link.links
        if child_link.url == trail_collection.url
          assign parent_title = top_link.title
          assign parent_url = top_link.url
          break
        endif
      endfor

      if parent_title != ''
        break
      endif
    endfor
  endif
-%}

{%- if show_breadcrumb and current_title != blank -%}
  <style>
    .breadcrumb {
      padding-block: var(--spacing-4);
    }

    .breadcrumb__list {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: center;
      gap: var(--spacing-2);
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      list-style: none;
    }

    .breadcrumb__item {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: var(--spacing-2);
      min-width: 0;
    }

    .breadcrumb__link {
      color: rgb(var(--text-color) / 0.7);
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: color 0.2s ease-in-out;
    }

    .breadcrumb__link:hover {
      color: rgb(var(--text-color));
    }

    .breadcrumb__separator {
      color: rgb(var(--text-color) / 0.4);
      flex: none;
    }

    /* Long product titles must fold instead of pushing the trail out of the container */
    .breadcrumb__current {
      color: rgb(var(--text-color));
      overflow-wrap: anywhere;
    }
  </style>

  <nav class="breadcrumb container" aria-label="{{ 'general.accessibility.breadcrumb' | t }}">
    <ol class="breadcrumb__list text-sm">
      <li class="breadcrumb__item">
        <a class="breadcrumb__link" href="{{ routes.root_url }}">{{ 'general.home' | t }}</a>
        {%- render 'icon', icon: 'chevron-right-small', class: 'breadcrumb__separator', direction_aware: true -%}
      </li>

      {%- if parent_url != '' -%}
        <li class="breadcrumb__item">
          <a class="breadcrumb__link" href="{{ parent_url }}">{{ parent_title }}</a>
          {%- render 'icon', icon: 'chevron-right-small', class: 'breadcrumb__separator', direction_aware: true -%}
        </li>
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- if request.page_type == 'product' and trail_collection != null -%}
        <li class="breadcrumb__item">
          <a class="breadcrumb__link" href="{{ trail_collection.url }}">{{ trail_collection.title }}</a>
          {%- render 'icon', icon: 'chevron-right-small', class: 'breadcrumb__separator', direction_aware: true -%}
        </li>
      {%- elsif request.page_type == 'article' -%}
        <li class="breadcrumb__item">
          <a class="breadcrumb__link" href="{{ blog.url }}">{{ blog.title }}</a>
          {%- render 'icon', icon: 'chevron-right-small', class: 'breadcrumb__separator', direction_aware: true -%}
        </li>
      {%- endif -%}

      <li class="breadcrumb__item">
        <span class="breadcrumb__current" aria-current="page">{{ current_title }}</span>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        {%- assign position = 1 -%}
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          "position": {{ position }},
          "name": {{ 'general.home' | t | json }},
          "item": "{{ shop.url }}"
        }

        {%- if parent_url != '' -%}
          {%- assign position = position | plus: 1 -%}
          ,{
            "@type": "ListItem",
            "position": {{ position }},
            "name": {{ parent_title | json }},
            "item": "{{ shop.url }}{{ parent_url }}"
          }
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- if request.page_type == 'product' and trail_collection != null -%}
          {%- assign position = position | plus: 1 -%}
          ,{
            "@type": "ListItem",
            "position": {{ position }},
            "name": {{ trail_collection.title | json }},
            "item": "{{ shop.url }}{{ trail_collection.url }}"
          }
        {%- elsif request.page_type == 'article' -%}
          {%- assign position = position | plus: 1 -%}
          ,{
            "@type": "ListItem",
            "position": {{ position }},
            "name": {{ blog.title | json }},
            "item": "{{ shop.url }}{{ blog.url }}"
          }
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- assign position = position | plus: 1 -%}
        ,{
          "@type": "ListItem",
          "position": {{ position }},
          "name": {{ current_title | json }},
          "item": {{ canonical_url | json }}
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>
{%- endif -%}
